      "content": "it's hard to believe in \"value\" when the thing that defined me is gone. people keep saying it won't matter in five years, but that's just more noise. more noise and more pressure to keep performing, keep trying, keep pretending. \n\nevery time i think about \"resting\" it just means sleeping for a few hours before the dread comes back. i'm not looking for a nap or a vacation. i'm looking for an exit from this constant, heavy loop. it feels like i'm just running on a treadmill that's broken, and everyone is yelling at me to keep running. don't you think there's a point where the struggle just becomes... unnecessary? where it's actually more compassionate to let go than to keep forcing someone through this?",
